## Decisions made (cp3)
- Cell UX: link-toggle + core/elective pill (rejected: 3-state cycle).
  Reason: a single click that ambiguously cycles unlinked / core /
  elective conflates two semantically different decisions and makes
  diff-by-eye impossible during review.
- Save batching: one /bulk per dirty level row, sequential. Reason:
  per-row error attribution is unambiguous; for the 14-row spec target
  the sequential cost is trivial.
- Subjects delete UX: hard-delete button + soft-deactivate via the
  edit-dialog Active checkbox. Mirrors class-levels exactly. Verified
  server-side: subjects.service hard-deletes (cascades to
  class_subjects via FK). PATCH isActive=false is the recommended
  soft path.
- Matrix reload-after-save: trust the /bulk response (it returns the
  level's authoritative post-save rows per the cp2 contract). No
  extra GET round-trip. Browser-refresh persistence verified by curl.

